The Cinema Exhibitors Association of Nigeria (CEAN) has announced movies to be exhibited at various cinemas across the country during the Easter celebration. Its National Chairman, Mr Patrick Lee, disclosed this while speaking with the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Friday in Lagos.   I’m about to build ‘craziest crib ever’-…     Davido sets to develop gift land from dad     Rick Ross arrives Lagos 10 years after for Easter concert   Lee listed the movies as: Sonic The Hedgehog 2, King of Thieves, Ben From Downstairs, Fantastic Beasts: The Secret of Dumbledore, The Blood Covenant and Twenty Nine. He noted that cinemas were set to excite movie lovers in beautiful ambience to enjoy films of their choice. “We invite movie lovers to visit cinemas close to their location and watch these movies,” he said. (NAN)